\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. A. minus} Bernh., {\i Syst. Verz. Erfurt} 154 (1800) ({\i Lappa minor} Hill). Plant 50-150 cm. Basal leaves up to 50 cm, broadly ovate, cordate; petioles hollow. Each main branch of inflorescence racemose, the terminal capitula usually solitary. Involucre 15-18 × 15-25 mm in fruit, globose, green or purple-tinged, often with dense arachnoid indumentum when young, becoming subglabrous, closed in fruit. Florets longer than involucral bracts. Achenes 5-7 mm, brownish; pappus 1-3·5 mm. 2n = 36.{\i  Most of Europe except the arctic.} All except Az Cr Fa Is Sb.
\par

