\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. A. nemorosum} Lej., {\i Mag. Hort.} ({\i Liège}){\b  1}: 289 (1833). Plant 100-250 cm. Basal leaves up to 50 cm, broadly ovate, cordate; petioles hollow. Each main branch of inflorescence racemose, often terminating in a cluster of three capitula. Involucre 20-25 × 30-35 mm in fruit, ovoid, subsessile, green or tinged with dark purple, usually with sparse arachnoid indumentum, closed in fruit. Florets about as long as involucral bracts. Achenes 6-9 mm, dark brown; pappus 1-3·5 mm. 2n = 36.{\i  Much of Europe, but rare in the south and parts of the north.} Au Be Br Bu Cz Da Fe Ga Ge Hb He Hu It Ju No Po Rm Rs (C, W, K, E) Su.
