\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 113.         Cousinia}            Cass.
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc By D.M. Moore
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Perennial herbs. Leaves alternate, simple. Capitula few. Involucral bracts imbricate, the outer with recurved apical spines. Receptacular scales scarious, twisted, glabrous. Florets all tubular, hermaphrodite. Anthers with pinnate basal appendages. Achenes obpyramidal, with 4 narrowly winged angles; pappus a short, dentate corona.
